.TH "blk_abort_request" 9 "blk_abort_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blk_abort_request \- Request recovery for the specified command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" blk_abort_request
.BI "(struct request *req "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "req" 12
pointer to the request of interest
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function requests that the block layer start recovery for the
request by deleting the timer and calling the q's timeout function.
LLDDs who implement their own error recovery MAY ignore the timeout
event if they generated blk_abort_request.
